comments.body:
To reduce the scope for spurious settings changes, I think it makes sense to compare the version to a specific version (where the default was changed) for each upgrader case.
E.g.

``` c++
int settingsVersion = settings.value(strSettingsVersionKey);
if (settingsVersion < 130000 && settings.contains("nDatabaseCache") && settings.value("nDatabaseCache") == 100)
```

